Title: Object: Sepulchres of Arabian saints near Rosetta
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 23 in volume I: five men standing in front of two domes in the centre, a woman and a naked child walking along a path towards the men, a man with a turban and a stick walking along the path in the left foreground, another dome behind a tower in the left background; after Mayer; published state. 1801 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.I.23)
